meta {
  name: 23 Support Info (SiteAdmin)
  seq: 23
}

docs {
  # Support Info (SiteAdmin)

  SiteAdmin-authored **support / help information** — HTML help content tied to a
  screen (Request URL), categorised by a Meta Type and a Business/Branch
  audience. Records are **platform-level** (CLAUDE.md §4.2): they carry **no
  `tenant_id` and no RLS**, are authored once by SiteAdmin, and are shared across
  every business.

  - **Base path:** `{{baseUrl}}/siteadmin/support-info`
  - **Auth:** SiteAdmin JWT only (`Authorization: Bearer {{siteAdminToken}}`).
    `@Public()` opts these routes out of the business `JwtAuthGuard`; the
    `SiteAdminPermissionGuard` validates the `jwt-siteadmin` token and permission.
    A business token is rejected — the two token types are not interchangeable.
  - **Permissions:** reads require `master-data:read`, writes require
    `master-data:write` (cumulative role **content_admin and above** —
    content_admin → operations_admin → full_admin → super_owner).
  - **Response envelope:** success → `{ success: true, data, meta: { timestamp, … } }`;
    list responses lift `total / page / limit / totalPages` into `meta`. Errors →
    `{ success: false, error: { code, message } }`.

  ---

  ## Data model — `SupportInfo` (`support_infos`)

  | Field         | Type                          | Notes                                                        |
  | ------------- | ----------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
  | `id`          | string (uuid)                 | server-generated                                             |
  | `metaType`    | string **(required)**         | category tag; searchable                                     |
  | `code`        | string \| null                | user-supplied, **NOT unique**; searchable                    |
  | `title`       | string **(required)**         | **globally unique among active rows** (reusable after delete)|
  | `tenantType`  | enum `BUSINESS` \| `BRANCH` **(required)** | audience tag (not a scoping column)             |
  | `status`      | enum `ACTIVE` \| `INACTIVE`   | defaults to `ACTIVE`                                          |
  | `requestUrl`  | string \| null                | the screen/URL the help is attached to                       |
  | `helpContent` | string **(required)**         | full HTML body (stored as Postgres `text`)                   |
  | `createdBy` / `updatedBy` | string \| null    | authoring SiteAdmin id (SiteAdmin routes aren't audit-logged)|
  | `createdAt` / `updatedAt` / `deletedAt` | datetime | soft delete: `deletedAt = NULL` means active            |

  ---

  ## Endpoints

  ### POST `/siteadmin/support-info` — create · `master-data:write`
  Body (JSON): `metaType`* , `code?`, `title`* , `tenantType`* , `status?`,
  `requestUrl?`, `helpContent`* . Returns the created record (**201**). `title`
  must be unique among active rows → **409 `SUPPORT_INFO_TITLE_CONFLICT`**;
  invalid/missing fields → **400** (class-validator; unknown props rejected).

  ### GET `/siteadmin/support-info` — list · `master-data:read`
  Query: `page` (default 1), `limit` (default 20, max 100), `search`
  (case-insensitive over `metaType` OR `code`; whitespace-only ignored), `status`
  (`ACTIVE`/`INACTIVE`). Ordered newest-first by `updatedAt`. Each item is
  projected to **exactly** `{ id, metaType, code, title, updatedAt, tenantType,
  status }` (the full `helpContent` is only returned by Get). Pagination in `meta`.

  ### GET `/siteadmin/support-info/:id` — get one · `master-data:read`
  Returns the full record incl. `helpContent`. Missing/soft-deleted →
  **404 `SUPPORT_INFO_NOT_FOUND`**.

  ### PATCH `/siteadmin/support-info/:id` — update · `master-data:write`
  Partial body (all fields optional). A changed `title` is re-validated for
  uniqueness → **409 `SUPPORT_INFO_TITLE_CONFLICT`**. Sets `updatedBy`.
  Missing → **404**.

  ### DELETE `/siteadmin/support-info/:id` — soft delete · `master-data:write`
  Sets `deletedAt`; the title is freed for reuse. Missing → **404**.

  ---

  ## Error codes

  | HTTP | `error.code`                  | When                                             |
  | ---- | ----------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
  | 400  | (validation)                  | missing/invalid field, bad enum, unknown property |
  | 401  | `UNAUTHORISED`                | no / invalid / non-SiteAdmin token               |
  | 403  | `FORBIDDEN`                   | SiteAdmin lacks the required `master-data:*` perm |
  | 404  | `SUPPORT_INFO_NOT_FOUND`      | id missing or soft-deleted                        |
  | 409  | `SUPPORT_INFO_TITLE_CONFLICT` | title already used by an active record            |

  ---

  ## End-to-end run order

  Only `siteAdminToken` is needed — no business login or tenant. Run
  **SiteAdmin Auth → Login** (`admin@kalnostics.com` / `SuperSecret1`) first,
  then this folder in sequence:

  1. **Create Support Info** — 201; captures `supportInfoId` + `supportInfoTitle`.
  2. **List Support Info** — 200; verifies the projection + `meta` pagination.
  3. **Get Support Info** — 200; full record.
  4. **Update Support Info** — 200; status/helpContent change.
  5. **Create Support Info - Duplicate Title** — 409 (reuses `supportInfoTitle`).
  6. **Create Support Info - Missing Required Field** — 400.
  7. **Delete Support Info** — 200; soft delete.
  8. **Get Support Info - Not Found** — 404 (the now-deleted id).
  9. **List Support Info - Unauthorized** — 401 (no token).

  The post-response scripts populate the runtime vars automatically. Select the
  **Local** environment first.
}
